	<refnamediv>
		<refname>fitellipse</refname>

		<refpurpose>Fits an ellipse around a set of 2D points.</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>

		<synopsis> [a,b,c,e,f]=fitellipse(points);</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection>

		<title>Parameters</title>

		<variablelist>                                                                            
			<varlistentry><term>points:</term>
				<listitem><para>matrix containing x and y coordinates of all points.</para></listitem></varlistentry>      
                        <varlistentry><term>a</term>        
				<listitem><para>Width of rotated rectangle returned by the function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
                        <varlistentry><term>b</term>        
				<listitem><para>Height of rotated rectangle returned by the function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
                        <varlistentry><term>c</term>        
				<listitem><para>x coordinate of center of rotated rectangle returned by function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
                        <varlistentry><term>d</term>        
				<listitem><para>The rotation angle in a clockwise direction .</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
                        <varlistentry><term>e</term>        
				<listitem><para>.</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
                                                                 
		</variablelist>

	</refsection>



	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para> Fits an ellipse around a set of 2D points.</para>
	
		<para>The function calculates the ellipse that fits (in a least-squares sense) a set of 2D points best of all. It returns the rotated rectangle in which the ellipse is inscribed.</para>

		<para>It is expected that the user input should be matrix containing a and y coordinates of all points and the function will return dimensions of rotated rectangle in which ellipse is inscribed .
		</para>
		
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Examples</title>
                <programlisting role="example">d=[0,0,10,0,10,10,5,4,2,2,5,4];&#10;[a,b,c,e,f]=fitellipse(d);</programlisting>
	</refsection>

